Statistics

The decoder could continuously calculate things like:

Estimated WPM
Average WPM
Tone frequency
Signal duration
Decode confidence (rather than "accuracy", because with an unknown incoming signal you don't know the true message)
Number of decoded characters
Number of words

For live decoding, confidence is a better metric than accuracy. Accuracy only makes sense when the expected text is known, such as in Practice mode.
Possible display:

CW Decoder

WPM: 18.7
Tone: 702 Hz
Quality: 94%

CQ CQ DE SM7ABC
K

or

Decoded:
CQ CQ DE SM7ABC K

18.5 WPM
94% confidence
702 Hz
Future possibilities

Once the decoder exists, there are a lot of interesting additions:

Automatic speed detection
Automatic tone detection
Noise filter
Character timing visualization
Dot/dash timing graph
Display the raw Morse (.-.-) alongside decoded text
Save decoded text to memory
USB serial output to a PC


